{"article_id":"qVAxfXCbMNLrIGlC","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Good news about the coronavirus is in short supply .","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"The United States ' confirmed case count is approaching half a million","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"- more than triple any other country ' s .","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"The U.S. will soon lead the world in COVID-19 deaths as well .","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"Roughly 95 percent of Americans are living under lockdown orders .","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"No one seems to have any real sense of how or when this will end .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"But look a little harder","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"and you can just start to discern a faint light at the end of this very dark tunnel .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"You just have to know where to look .","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"Ignore the skyrocketing case count ,","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"or at least take it with a grain of salt .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"As FiveThirtyEight ' s Nate Silver has explained ,","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"the number of positive tests","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"reported in any given city , state or country is highly dependent on the number of tests","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"conducted there","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"-","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"which differs wildly from place to place over time .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"Death tolls are more useful","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"for comparing how the epidemic is evolving in different locales .","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"because it typically takes weeks for someone with COVID-19 to die ,","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"they ' re also lagging indicators","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that tell you less about where on its epidemic trajectory the virus is now","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"than where it was back then .","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"The number","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"you really want to focus on","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"is hospitalizations .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"And","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"if it ' s good news you ' re after ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"pay particular attention to what ' s happening in two key states :","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"New York and California .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"Until very recently , nationwide data","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"about how many COVID-19 patients are currently receiving treatment in hospitals","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"was hard to come by .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"It ' s still incomplete and inconsistent .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"But on April 7 , researchers at the University of Minnesota launched the U.S. COVID-19 Hospitalization Tracking Project ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"which is just what it sounds like :","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"the first effort","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"to capture , track , visualize and compare daily data on the number of COVID-19 hospitalizations from the 37 state departments of health","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"that are reporting this information","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"( so far ) .","depth":12},{"id":41,"text":"The reason this information is so valuable is simple .","depth":4},{"id":42,"text":"Because hospitalization typically occurs a week or so after infection ,","depth":5},{"id":43,"text":"it ' s less of a lagging indicator than the death count","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"( which trails by two to two and a half weeks )","depth":7},{"id":45,"text":"and more directly tied to the trajectory of the epidemic than the testing-dependent case count .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"It ' s also a measure of the most pressing public health concern of all :","depth":4},{"id":47,"text":"how close we are to exceeding the capacity of our hospital system ,","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"which can make COVID-19 much deadlier","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"than it would otherwise be .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"Which brings us to New York and California .","depth":4},{"id":51,"text":"Chart each state ' s hospitalization data over the last seven days or so ,","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"and two different narratives emerge .","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"Each day this week , New York Gov . Andrew Cuomo has delivered a cautiously optimistic message at his morning briefing .","depth":4},{"id":54,"text":"\" We are reaching a plateau in the total number of hospitalizations , \"","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"Cuomo said Tuesday .","depth":7},{"id":56,"text":"\" You can see the growth ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"and you see","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"it ' s starting to flatten . \"","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"\" All of this data suggests","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"we are flattening the curve so far , \"","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"he added Thursday .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"\" So far our efforts are working .","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"They ' re working better","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"than anyone projected","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"they would work . \"","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"The hospitalization numbers tell the tale .","depth":3},{"id":67,"text":"On Wednesday , New York ' s daily death count hit an all-time high :","depth":5},{"id":68,"text":"799 .","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"But that reflects infections from weeks ago ,","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"before the state ' s lockdown started .","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"The number of people","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"testing positive","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"stayed relatively flat .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":147,"left":123,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":114,"right":122,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":114,"left":82,"right":113,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":82,"left":81,"right":8,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":81,"left":78,"right":80,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":78,"left":0,"right":77,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":77,"left":7